messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
There's a mention 911.
What is the address of the emergency?
See, I think some people are shooting.
Okay, give me that address again, please.
Okay, and it's a test.
What phone number are you calling from?
Please tell somebody to hurry.
Do you see anybody shooting or do you hear it only?
I hear it.
What do you hear? How does it sound?
I'm not sure.
Did you want to leave your name?
Yep.
Did you want to speak to the police when they got out there?
I'm not sure. I need to call my mom, so…
Okay. Did you want to speak to the police?
No, can you just please send somebody as soon as possible?
They'll be there as soon as possible, okay?
Thank you.
All right. Bye.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
We need to send some officers over here on Blueford Street. They are shooting like crazy.
Blueford and what intersection?
Blueford and Reginald Street.
Did you see who is doing the shooting?
No, ma'am. I'm on the floor. They just shooting all around.
Do you need me to have an officer come talk to you?
No, ma'am. Just tell them to get these folks off the street.
Is there anybody hurt in your house?
No, ma'am. Just a lot of shooting outside.
Okay. They'll be there as soon as possible.
Thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
We need an ambulance out here. Somebody just got shot.
What is the address of your emergency?
We're at the park, at the basketball courts.
I'm getting help to you. Are you with the patient now?
Yes, he's bleeding a lot. Hurry up.
Okay, I'm going to tell you how to help him. Just stay on the line with me, okay? How old is he?
I don't know, he's a teenager, maybe?
I'm sending an ambulance while we're talking. Is the assailant still nearby?
No, they drove off. It was a drive-by shooting.
Do you know what they were driving?
No, I ducked when I heard the shots.
That's okay. Is there any serious bleeding?
Yes, a lot.
What part of the body was injured?
The leg, I think.
Is there more than one wound?
I don't know, there's a lot of blood.
I'm going to tell you how to control the bleeding. Do you have a clean, dry cloth or towel?
Yes, hang on.
Place it on the wound and press down firmly. Do not lift it up to look.
Okay, I'm doing that now.
Is the bleeding controlled?
I think so.
Do you see the police?
Yes, they're here now.
Okay, let them take over. You're doing great.
Thank you, ma'am.
You're welcome. Take care.
